1
00:00:45,439 --> 00:00:45,679
Hello.

2
00:00:45,759 --> 00:00:46,000
Hello.

3
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:47,880
Anti-Triad Chief Inspector Chen Jiadong.

4
00:00:48,679 --> 00:00:49,399
I'm also the commander

5
00:00:49,399 --> 00:00:50,799
of this Portland Street operation.

6
00:00:50,799 --> 00:00:51,600
Hello.

7
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:53,920
Liu Zhenfeng, Major Crimes Inspector.

8
00:00:54,399 --> 00:00:54,960
Here to assist the investigation.

9
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:56,759
I'm Chen Hua, sent by the Mainland

10
00:00:57,119 --> 00:00:58,719
Ministry of Public Security to coordinate.

11
00:00:59,119 --> 00:01:01,280
This time, Anti-Triad, Major Crimes,

12
00:01:01,399 --> 00:01:03,079
and Mainland Public Security join forces.

13
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:04,359
This is deeply significant.

14
00:01:04,359 --> 00:01:05,079
I won't waste words.

15
00:01:05,079 --> 00:01:06,159
Let's get straight to the point.

16
00:01:06,159 --> 00:01:06,840
All right.

17
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:09,799
According to witness testimony,

18
00:01:09,799 --> 00:01:11,879
before the victim Wang Danni fell,

19
00:01:11,879 --> 00:01:13,560
she was caught up in a triad brawl.

20
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,120
The suspect Liang Zhiqiang

21
00:01:15,319 --> 00:01:16,519
was once convicted of premeditated murder

22
00:01:16,519 --> 00:01:18,439
and sentenced to 20 years in prison.

23
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,079
He was released just six months ago.

24
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:22,000
This Liang Zhiqiang,

25
00:01:22,359 --> 00:01:24,599
was a triad member before going to prison.

26
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,920
He had quite a name in Heyisheng.

27
00:01:28,599 --> 00:01:30,400
In your city, they call it a "Top..."

28
00:01:31,359 --> 00:01:31,760
"Top..."

29
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,239
It's called a Top Enforcer.

30
00:01:33,319 --> 00:01:34,680
Right, a Top Enforcer.

31
00:01:35,719 --> 00:01:38,159
He and Xie Guanhong, now in Heyisheng,

32
00:01:38,239 --> 00:01:40,239
are brothers who grew up together.

33
00:01:40,879 --> 00:01:42,439
After Liang Zhiqiang got out this time,

34
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:44,079
he's been in contact with Heyisheng.

35
00:01:44,239 --> 00:01:45,040
Officer Chen,

36
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,120
you've dealt with him for over 20 years.

37
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:49,959
You're practically brothers.

38
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,519
My informant

39
00:01:56,519 --> 00:01:58,480
has tracked down Liang Zhiqiang.

40
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:01,760
Everything is under our control.

41
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,599
Live a good life after you get out

42
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:49,439
You okay?

43
00:02:53,879 --> 00:02:54,680
I'm fine.

44
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:51,000
This place used to be a total mess

45
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:54,280
Now it's all neat and tidy

46
00:03:54,319 --> 00:03:57,319
Old buildings replaced by new ones.

47
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:59,199
There are so many new subway lines now

48
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,000
You can get anywhere easily

49
00:04:01,599 --> 00:04:03,560
Everything you see now

50
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,479
it all belongs to me,

51
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,599
Xie Guanhong.

52
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,960
It's changed so much

53
00:04:15,879 --> 00:04:16,680
I hardly recognize it

54
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,240
Twenty years

55
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,079
What place doesn't change?

56
00:04:23,439 --> 00:04:24,800
But I believe

57
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:27,800
some things never change

58
00:04:30,639 --> 00:04:31,439
A Qiang

59
00:04:43,759 --> 00:04:44,600
Uncle Xiang.

60
00:04:46,199 --> 00:04:47,240
You're back.

61
00:04:47,839 --> 00:04:48,639
Good to have you back.

62
00:04:55,079 --> 00:04:56,199
Twenty years.

63
00:04:57,199 --> 00:04:58,240
You've finally returned.

64
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,800
Now I've got another hand to help me.

65
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,360
I don't want to go back to the gang.

66
00:05:15,319 --> 00:05:18,000
You were Heyisheng's Top Enforcer.

67
00:05:18,079 --> 00:05:19,759
You can't just walk away like that.

68
00:05:20,879 --> 00:05:22,279
Think you can wash that off?

69
00:05:22,639 --> 00:05:24,160
Twenty years have gone by.

70
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,959
And I've figured one thing out.

71
00:05:28,759 --> 00:05:29,680
All I want now

72
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,959
is to find an ordinary job

73
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,319
and live like an ordinary person.

74
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,040
The grudges of the underworld,

75
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:36,720
all the fighting and killing,

76
00:05:37,399 --> 00:05:38,800
it's not for me anymore.

77
00:05:44,319 --> 00:05:45,319
Brother Hong.

78
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:46,920
Brother Hong.

79
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,000
You're back, A Qiang.

80
00:05:56,319 --> 00:05:57,319
Cannon.

81
00:05:58,079 --> 00:05:59,680
Good to see you back.

82
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,480
Today, I'm a happy man.

83
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:04,959
And why's that?

84
00:06:05,439 --> 00:06:07,360
Because our Liang Zhiqiang,

85
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,800
Brother Qiang, is back!

86
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:14,920
Brother Qiang did great things for us.

87
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,759
And he was the Top Enforcer, too.

88
00:06:17,879 --> 00:06:18,759
Come on.

89
00:06:18,759 --> 00:06:20,399
Let's raise a toast to Brother Qiang.

90
00:06:20,439 --> 00:06:22,160
Brother Qiang, cheers!

91
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,199
Bottoms up!

92
00:06:23,199 --> 00:06:24,120
Cheers!

93
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,600
And our gang, you know,

94
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:38,120
it's time for a new election.

95
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,680
Now that Brother Qiang is back,

96
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,839
I, Cannon, am dropping out of the race,

97
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:44,040
and I nominate our Brother Qiang

98
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,360
to be the new Dragon Head.

99
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,120
What do you all say?

100
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,319
Yes!

101
00:06:47,319 --> 00:06:49,519
Brother Qiang! Brother Qiang!

102
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,199
Brother Qiang!

103
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,800
Ah Hong.

104
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,639
Will you back Brother Qiang

105
00:06:57,639 --> 00:07:00,800
to be the new Dragon Head?

106
00:07:14,519 --> 00:07:15,160
Ah Hong

107
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:15,600
Ah Hong

108
00:07:16,319 --> 00:07:16,959
What are you doing?

109
00:07:16,959 --> 00:07:17,399
What are you doing?

110
00:07:18,639 --> 00:07:19,079
Ah Hong

111
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,120
Don't worry, Brother Pao.

112
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,279
It's an act.

113
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,519
Just an act, that's all.

114
00:07:35,519 --> 00:07:39,000
Nice acting, real nice acting.

115
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:50,800
A Pao, Ah Hong had a bit too much.

116
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,120
Let me apologize to you on his behalf.

117
00:07:53,759 --> 00:07:54,680
A Qiang...

118
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:57,839
Only you treat Xie Guanhong as a brother.

119
00:08:00,079 --> 00:08:01,920
The gang changes leadership this year.

120
00:08:02,839 --> 00:08:05,680
You did 20 years in jail for the gang.

121
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:08,079
You've more than earned that seat.

122
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:10,160
Don't joke around, Brother Pao.

123
00:08:10,319 --> 00:08:12,720
Everyone knows what kind of man you are.

124
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,000
Just tell me the truth.

125
00:08:14,639 --> 00:08:15,560
Back then...

126
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:17,480
did Xie Guanhong kill Brother Long?

127
00:08:27,839 --> 00:08:29,240
You killed Brother Long back then

128
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,319
and now you've got the nerve to sit here?

129
00:08:30,319 --> 00:08:30,879
A Pao

130
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,600
It's been 20 years.

131
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,960
Why bring this up again?

132
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:01,000
Brother Qiang.

133
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,639
Don't.

134
00:09:02,879 --> 00:09:03,679
No need to be so formal.

135
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,600
Brother Qiang.

136
00:09:14,559 --> 00:09:16,200
Do you actually think

137
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:18,440
that from now on, every time I see you,

138
00:09:18,919 --> 00:09:21,279
I'll have to bow and grovel like this?

139
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:29,360
The Top Enforcer.

140
00:09:30,279 --> 00:09:31,600
The Top Enforcer.

141
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,879
So impressive.

142
00:09:34,559 --> 00:09:36,440
No wonder you got to rot in jail.

143
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:39,399
I just idolize you, Brother Qiang.

144
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:41,000
What are you getting at?

145
00:09:50,679 --> 00:09:53,360
Just chatting, Brother Qiang.

146
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,360
Don't read too much into it.

147
00:09:56,399 --> 00:09:57,679
I just think

148
00:09:58,799 --> 00:10:02,080
some people keep living off past glories,

149
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:04,080
thinking because they earned some merit,

150
00:10:04,559 --> 00:10:06,240
they forget who the hell they are.

151
00:10:06,679 --> 00:10:08,159
Thinking now that they're back,

152
00:10:08,159 --> 00:10:11,480
everyone must line up and kowtow to them.

153
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:13,360
But

154
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:15,759
we, the ones doing the heavy lifting now,

155
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:17,960
aren't buying that anymore.

156
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,480
I've got zero interest

157
00:10:19,679 --> 00:10:21,399
in your fight for the top spot.

158
00:10:22,559 --> 00:10:24,200
But since getting out, it's true,

159
00:10:24,639 --> 00:10:26,120
I've noticed things aren't like before.

160
00:10:27,679 --> 00:10:28,879
Guys who used to just talk big

161
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,519
never lasted very long.

162
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,159
So you earned some merit, big deal.

163
00:10:33,279 --> 00:10:34,320
Liang Zhiqiang.

164
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:37,399
You think you can still keep control now?

165
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:39,200
What really happened 20 years ago,

166
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,799
who's to say?

167
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,759
What happened 20 years ago,

168
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,360
you don't know.

169
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,080
But I do.

170
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,200
Do you still hate me?

171
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,120
Honestly,

172
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:57,879
I did hate you.

173
00:10:58,759 --> 00:10:59,720
And I hated Bao Jiao too.

174
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,240
Back then I kept wondering

175
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,759
why my best brother

176
00:11:04,799 --> 00:11:06,360
and the woman I loved most at the time

177
00:11:07,279 --> 00:11:08,480
would do something like that,

178
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:10,720
would betray me.

179
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,559
But after all this time,

180
00:11:15,559 --> 00:11:17,159
I've thought it through clearly.

181
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:19,759
Back then, if it weren't for you,

182
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,080
who knows where Bao Jiao would be.

183
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,159
So I don't hate you.

184
00:11:35,639 --> 00:11:36,679
Xie Zihao

185
00:11:36,679 --> 00:11:38,200
Drag racing in this heavy rain...

186
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:39,960
You're really just like your dad

187
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,240
You only pick up the bad habits

188
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:41,879
Mom

189
00:11:42,279 --> 00:11:42,919
I'm all grown up now

190
00:11:42,919 --> 00:11:44,000
What's wrong with heading out a bit late?

191
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,120
I'll be back soon

192
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:48,759
Xie Zihao

193
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,600
It's fine

194
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,320
Thanks

195
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:00,200
Xie Guanhong

196
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,200
Just how much did you drink?

197
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:03,840
You weigh a ton

198
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,000
Careful there

199
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,639
You two, one racing cars, one boozing

200
00:12:08,159 --> 00:12:09,360
Honestly, the pair of you

201
00:12:10,159 --> 00:12:10,919
Lili

202
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,360
Lili, my ass!

203
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:14,200
Why's your figure gone downhill?

204
00:12:51,399 --> 00:12:52,200
Mom

205
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:53,799
What are you looking at?

206
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:03,600
Nothing

207
00:13:26,559 --> 00:13:29,799
You think one ring is enough to marry me?

208
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,360
Me, Bao Jiao,

209
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,159
when I get married,

210
00:13:33,159 --> 00:13:35,519
it has to be a proper, grand wedding.

211
00:13:35,519 --> 00:13:37,159
Nothing less than the grandest send-off.

212
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:37,759
You got that?

213
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:38,879
Of course.

214
00:13:38,879 --> 00:13:40,279
Liang Zhiqiang's woman,

215
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,840
must have a grand wedding, obviously.
